DESCRIPTION:Language Exchange Toronto - Se Habla English & Spanish\n**Spanish Language Conversation Toronto** is part of ***Se Habla***\, a worldwide community made up of 9 Meetup groups from 9 different cities across 6 countries. Join us and don't miss the opportunity to speak with native speakers.\n\n**Five years of meeting online.** Don’t wait—become part of our supportive international network of like-minded people and make friends all over the world. Free forever after One-Time Donation.\n\n**We meet on the following days:**\n\n* Monday 8 pm\n* Wednesday 8 pm\n* Friday 8 pm\n* Saturday 1 pm\n* Sunday 11 am\n\nThe average attendance per meeting is 25 participants.\n\n**Format**\nDepending on attendance and nationality\, small groups are formed with 4-6 people:\n\n* 2 native English speakers\n* 2 native Spanish speakers\n* 1 native speaker of another language\n\nThe meetings last for 2 hours and are divided into 4 periods:\n\n* 30 minutes speaking in English\n* 30 minutes speaking in Spanish\n* 30 minutes speaking in English\n* 30 minutes speaking in Spanish\n\nPlease note that **we speak half of the time in English and half in Spanish.** We help each other learn both languages.\n\n**After two hours**\, everyone returns to the main room to meet all participants and take a group screenshot. If you have time\, you’re welcome to stay and continue the conversation for as long as you like.\n\n**Community**\n**We have 9 MeetUp groups meeting at the same time** (Mexico City\, Calgary\, Vancouver\, Toronto\, New York\, London\, Los Angeles\, Medellin\, and Santiago de Chile). However\, during the exchange\, you will meet people not only from these cities but also from all over the world.\n\nYou can get the link to our 9 MeetUp groups by visiting any of the following pages:\n[https://se-habla.com/spanish-meetup/](https://se-habla.com/spanish-meetup/)\n[https://se-habla.com/english-meetup/](https://se-habla.com/english-meetup/)\n\n**One-Time Donation**\nFor over four years\, the meetings were free\, but starting last October\, I am requesting a **ONE-TIME DONATION** to access the meetings and help to cover the costs of the 9 MeetUp Groups.\n\nYou can make the one-time donation at the link below. Afterward\, PayPal will redirect you to a page where you'll find the Zoom link to join the meeting.\n[https://se-habla.com/language-exchange/](https://se-habla.com/language-exchange/)\n\nIf you have already made a donation and don't have the Zoom link\, please contact me.\n\n**Please don’t hesitate to reach out if you have any further questions.**\n\nSee you soon\,\n**Héctor Fuentes**
